<@U026NB2U2> Just so you know, for the summary doc, it not only has a character limit, but it also has a one-page limit.
Do you want me to start cutting now?
i think before we cut further - is this a PDF we upload? or is it text pasted onto a field? What about the key words and titles? Do those go into a section?
It also has to be 10 point font :disappointed:

All documents uploaded to NSF Fastlane should follow the formatting rules:

Ariel, Courier New, or Palatino Linotype at a font size 10 or larger should be used; or
Times New Roman or Computer Modern fonts at a font size of 12 points or larger.
Proposals formatted with multiple columns are not accepted.
You can either upload or input text. I've been uploading
<@U026NB2U2> It needs the keywords but not the title

Project Summary (Limited to one page and includes paragraphs in the following areas with a total limit of 4,600 characters for all 3 areas:
Overview, Key Words, and Subtopic Name. 
Intellectual Merits. 
Broader/Commercial Impacts
We also need a Proposal/Project Title. What is this proposal called? (e.g. "Sommely Wine Inventory Management System")
I like it, just would make it “Sommely: Wine Inventory Management System"
Sommely: Find the Right Wine at the Right Time with Smart Inventory Management
We’re moving away from the find the right wine line...
Ah okay! good to know/
How about Sommely: Smart Wine Inventory Management
Bam

<@U0K8ZSHN0> <@U026NB2U2> Budget is currently $196,480. Max we can request is $225,000. Outstanding items include decision on Marc (consultant, senior personnel, other personnel) and “Other expenses” which would include assembly, shipping, cloud hosting, etc.
must use it all!
I can add 25k of ideas to it. Current meeting going over but plan was to spend time till 3 pm on this
Ok cool. Thanks. Reminder, excluded items include sales/marketing, production, biz dev or patent work

Accept away
